Show Kodi current state:ph_check_app_name -s -a Kodi | more
Start or switch to Kodi:startkodi.sh | more
Stop Kodi:stopkodi.sh force | more
Restart Kodi:restartkodi.sh | more
Install Kodi and integrate with PieHelper:confapps_ph.sh -p int -a Kodi
Remove Kodi from PieHelper and uninstall:confapps_ph.sh -p rem -a Kodi
Update Kodi to the latest version (only if installed as a package):ph_update_pkg $PH_KODI_PKG_NAME | more
List all available options for Kodi:confopts_ph.sh -p list -a Kodi | more
View the current value of Kodi option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Kodi -g
View the current value of Kodi option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Kodi -g -r
Change the value of read-write Kodi option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Kodi -s
Change the value of read-write Kodi option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Kodi -s -r
Set all Kodi options back to default:ph_set_all_options_to_default Kodi
Display help for Kodi option(s) (Variable expansion disabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Kodi -d
Display help for Kodi option(s) (Variable expansion enabled):confopts_ph.sh -p prompt -a Kodi -d -r
Display TTY currently allocated to Kodi:confapps_ph.sh -p tty -a Kodi | more
Move Kodi to another TTY:confapps_ph.sh -p move -a Kodi -t prompt
Go to Main menu:ph_show_menu Main
Go to Apps menu:ph_show_menu Apps
Return to previous screen:return
